<subSubSection id="6CBDD680FF1883E8FC975C46FA53F9C5" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph id="2418850BFF1883E8FC975C46FC2BFB26" blockId="165.[823,1476,1061,1598]" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1883E8FC975C46FC04FBC6" box="[851,916,1062,1085]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">Notes.</emphasis>
– The tribe 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF1883E8FBDB5C46FB17FBC6" box="[1055,1159,1062,1085]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Brassiceae">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1883E8FBDB5C46FB17FBC6" box="[1055,1159,1062,1085]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">Brassiceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is notoriously complex, and none of the current molecular phylogenetic studies provided satisfactory data that agree with the current generic delimitation based solely on morphology (see 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF1883E8FB105CE5FCFEFB46" author="WARWICK, S. I. &amp; C. SAUDER" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" pagination="467 - 483" refId="ref144809" refString="WARWICK, S. I. &amp; C. SAUDER (2005). Phylogeny of tribe Brassiceae (Brassicaceae) based on chloroplast restriction site polymorphisms and nuclear ribosomal internal transcribed spacer and chloroplast trnL intron sequences. Canad. J. Bot. 83: 467 - 483." type="journal article" year="2005">WARWICK &amp; SAUDER, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF1883E8FCBC5CC5FB18FB46" author="WARWICK, S. I. &amp; J. C. HALL" box="[888,1160,1189,1214]" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" pagination="19 - 36" refId="ref144762" refString="WARWICK, S. I. &amp; J. C. HALL (2009). Phylogeny of Brassica and wild relatives. In: GUPTA, S. (ed.), Biology and breeding of crucifers: 19 - 36. CRC Press." type="book chapter" year="2009">WARWICK &amp; HALL, 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF1883E8FB565CC5FAE5FB46" author="ARIAS, T. &amp; J. C. PIRES" box="[1170,1397,1189,1213]" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" pagination="980 - 988" refId="ref135761" refString="ARIAS, T. &amp; J. C. PIRES (2012). A fully resolved chloroplast phylogeny of the brassica crops and wild relatives (Brassicaceae: Brassiceae): novel clades and potential taxonomic implications. Taxon 61: 980 - 988." type="journal article" year="2012">ARIAS &amp; PIRES, 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF1883E8FABA5CC5FC20FB26" author="ARIAS, T. &amp; M. A &amp; BEILSTEIN, M. &amp; TANG, M. R." pageId="165" pageNumber="165" pagination="86 - 91" refId="ref135807" refString="ARIAS, T., M. A. BEILSTEIN, M. TANG, M. R. MCKAIN &amp; J. C. PIRES (2014). Diversification time among Brassica (Brassicaceae) crops suggest hybrid fomation after 20 million years of divergence. Amer. J. Bot. 101: 86 - 91." type="journal article" year="2014">ARIAS et al., 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2418850BFF1883E8FC975C85FACAFA46" blockId="165.[823,1476,1061,1598]" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">
Indeed, 
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1883E8FC6F5C86FB94FB06" box="[939,1028,1254,1277]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF1883E8FC6F5C86FB90FB06" box="[939,1024,1254,1277]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Brassica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Brassica</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which currently includes 44 species centered in the Mediterranean region and SW Asia, is polyphyletic and needs substantial nomenclatural adjustments to make it monophyletic. When that is done, the genus would be substantially smaller and may well end up including 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF1883E8FA915D06FA52FA86" box="[1365,1474,1381,1405]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Brassica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oleracea">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1883E8FA915D06FA52FA86" box="[1365,1474,1381,1405]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">B. oleracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1883E8FC855DE6FCDFFA66" box="[833,847,1414,1437]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">n</emphasis>
=9), 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF1883E8FCBF5DE6FC52FA66" box="[891,962,1414,1437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Brassica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rapa">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1883E8FCBF5DE6FC52FA66" box="[891,962,1414,1437]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">B. rapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1883E8FC155DE6FC4FFA66" box="[977,991,1414,1437]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">n</emphasis>
=10), and some of their wild relatives with such chromosome numbers (see 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF1883E8FB985DC5FADEFA46" author="SNOGERUP, S. &amp; M. GUSTAFSSON &amp; R. V. BOTHMER" box="[1116,1358,1445,1469]" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" pagination="271 - 365" refId="ref143518" refString="SNOGERUP, S., M. GUSTAFSSON &amp; R. V. BOTHMER (1990). Brassica sect. Brassica (Brassicaceae). 1. Taxonomy and variation. Willdenowia 19: 271 - 365." type="journal article" year="1990">SNOGERUP et al., 1990</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2418850BFF1883E8FC975DA5FA53F9C5" blockId="165.[823,1476,1061,1598]" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">
Therefore, with the exclusion of 
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1883E8FB6C5DA6FA9BFA26" box="[1192,1291,1478,1501]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF1883E8FB6C5DA6FA96FA26" box="[1192,1286,1478,1501]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cretica">B. cretica</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the other species retained here in 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF1883E8FC285D86FBAEFA06" box="[1004,1086,1510,1533]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Brassica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="165" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF1883E8FC285D86FBAEFA06" box="[1004,1086,1510,1533]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="165">Brassica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are only tentatively assigned to the genus, and detailed molecular, morphological, cytogenetic, and genomic studies would most likely assign them to other genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
